  "prompt": "What I have to do after I catch pokemon in pokemon go?",
  "response": "Okay, you've caught a Pok\u00e9mon in Pok\u00e9mon GO! Congrats! Here's a breakdown of what you can do next:\n\n**1. Assess Your Catch:**\n\n*   **Appraise:** The first thing you should do is appraise the Pok\u00e9mon. Tap on the Pok\u00e9mon, then the three lines in the lower right corner, and then \"Appraise.\" Your team leader (Candela, Blanche, or Spark) will give you information about the Pok\u00e9mon's IVs (Individual Values). This is a hidden stat that affects how strong a Pok\u00e9mon can become.\n    *   **Why Appraise?** IVs help you decide which Pok\u00e9mon to invest in. A Pok\u00e9mon with high IVs has the potential to be significantly stronger than one with low IVs.\n*   **Check the CP (Combat Power):**  CP is a general indicator of a Pok\u00e9mon's strength. Higher CP is generally better.  Compare it to other Pok\u00e9mon of the same species that you already own.\n*   **Check the Moveset:** The Pok\u00e9mon's moves are very important for battles in Raids, Gyms, and PvP. The moveset is also a hidden value.\n\n**2. Decide What to Do With the Pok\u00e9mon:**\n\n*   **Keep It:**\n    *   **High CP/Good IVs:** Definitely keep Pok\u00e9mon with high CP and good IVs, especially if it's a species you want to use for battles.\n    *   **Useful Moveset:** Keep Pok\u00e9mon with beneficial movesets for battle.\n    *   **Shiny/Hundo (100% IV) or Rare:** Even if the CP isn't super high, keep Shiny Pok\u00e9mon (different color variations), Hundos (100% IV Pok\u00e9mon), or Pok\u00e9mon that are rare in your area. They are collectors items, and can be useful in battles if powered up.\n*   **Transfer It:**\n    *   **Low CP/Poor IVs:** Transfer Pok\u00e9mon with low CP and poor IVs to Professor Willow for Candy.\n    *   **Duplicates:** Transfer duplicates of Pok\u00e9mon you already have a stronger version of, unless they are Shiny or have unique movesets.\n    *   **During Events:** Some events offer bonus Candy or Stardust for transferring Pok\u00e9mon, making it a good time to clear out your storage.\n\n**How to Transfer:**\n\n1.  Select the Pok\u00e9mon you want to transfer.\n2.  Scroll to the bottom of the Pok\u00e9mon's info page.\n3.  Tap \"Transfer.\"\n4.  Confirm your transfer.  *Be very careful, as this action is permanent!*\n\n**3. Actions You Can Take With Kept Pok\u00e9mon:**\n\n*   **Power Up:** If you have enough Candy and Stardust, you can power up your Pok\u00e9mon to increase its CP and stats. This is useful for battles.\n*   **Evolve:** If you have enough Candy for that species, you can evolve your Pok\u00e9mon into a stronger form. Evolving Pok\u00e9mon can unlock new movesets as well.\n*   **Buddy Pok\u00e9mon:** Set the Pok\u00e9mon as your buddy to earn candy as you walk. Certain Pok\u00e9mon require you to make them your buddy and complete specific tasks before they can evolve.\n*   **Use it in Battles:** Use your Pok\u00e9mon in Gym Battles, Raids, Team GO Rocket battles, or Trainer Battles (PvP).\n*   **Trade:** Trade Pok\u00e9mon with friends. Trading can improve a Pok\u00e9mon's IVs (though it's random) and can be necessary to evolve certain Pok\u00e9mon.\n*   **Mega Evolve:** Some Pok\u00e9mon can Mega Evolve into a temporary, even more powerful form. This requires Mega Energy, which you get from Mega Raids.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Stardust:** Stardust is a valuable resource used for powering up Pok\u00e9mon. Use it wisely. Prioritize powering up Pok\u00e9mon that are truly useful for battles.\n*   **Candy:** Candy is specific to each Pok\u00e9mon species (e.g., Pikachu Candy, Charmander Candy). You need Candy to power up and evolve Pok\u00e9mon. Catching Pok\u00e9mon, transferring Pok\u00e9mon, and walking with your Buddy Pok\u00e9mon are the main ways to obtain Candy.\n*   **Storage Space:** Your Pok\u00e9mon storage is limited.  Upgrade it with Pok\u00e9Coins if you find yourself constantly running out of space.\n*   **Events:** Pay attention to Pok\u00e9mon GO events, as they often offer bonuses to catching, transferring, and evolving Pok\u00e9mon.\n\n**In Summary:**\n\n1.  **Catch Pok\u00e9mon.**\n2.  **Appraise & Check Stats (CP, IVs, Moveset).**\n3.  **Decide to Keep or Transfer.**\n4.  **If Keeping: Power Up, Evolve, Use in Battles, Trade, Buddy.**\n5.  **Manage Stardust & Candy.**\n6.  **Stay Aware of Events.**\n\nBy following these steps, you'll be able to make the most of your Pok\u00e9mon catches and build a strong team! Good luck, Trainer!\n",
